Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Baddie
    An interface that all "Bad guy" classes should extend.
    Goodie
    An interface that all "Good guy" classes should extend.
    MovetoAble
    This interface is meant for classes which pieces can be moved to.
    Selectable
    This interface is meant for classes which represents a game piece.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Board
    This class represents the game Board, which holds the rules for the game and all of its pieces.
    Building
    This class represents a Building within the game, which can be robbed.
    Cop
    This class represents a Cop within the game, who can capture Bad guys.
    Dice
    This class represents a 6-sided dice.
    GameObject
    Abstract class representing any noun within the game.
    GameRules
    This class contains all the necessary variables and methods that the game may need to have.
    Grass
    This class represents a grass tile.
    LevelLayout
    This class contains a String that tells the level loader where to put the different objects in the game.
    MainMethod
    This class instantiates the Board class to the specified dimension and runs.
    Road
    This class represents a Road within the game, which pieces can travel to.
    Robber
    This class represents a Robber within the game, which can rob Buildings and be captured by Cops.
    Square
    This class represents a tile on the board within the game.
    SquareGraph
    Class that uses a list of Squares and their adjacent Squares to perform a Graph traversal.
